name: Rust Networking
tagline: The home of networking using the Rust programming language
body:
### Welcome to the Rust Networking Community

We're still in the process of setting up our little community of Rust Networkers (the kind involving clients, servers, peers and protocols... Rather than the social kind!), but here are some links to get you started:

 * [The Google Group](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/rust-networking)
 * The IRC Channel, [#rust-networking](irc://irc.mozilla.org/rust-networking) ([web link](https://client00.chat.mibbit.com/?server=irc.mozilla.org&channel=%23rust-networking)) on irc.mozilla.org
 * [The Subreddit](https://www.reddit.com/r/rust_networking)

We follow the [Rust Code of Conduct](https://www.rust-lang.org/conduct.html), so please give it a quick look over if you haven't already.
